investigation.title: During development, the Sku6 mutant roots engage different genes than wild type Col-0 roots, either on the ground or in spaceflight.
investigation.description: The wild type Col-0 plants and the Sku-6 mutant plants of the Col-0 background were germinated on ISS or on the ground and the gene expression profiles in roots at 4 days or 8 days were established. The Sku6 gene (At2g03680) codes for a protein that localizes to microtubule within the cortical array and putatively acting as an intramolecular linker.

project.title: Molecular Biology of Growth and Cell Remodeling within the Spaceflight Environment (NNX12AN69G)

publications.title: Root skewing-associated genes impact the spaceflight response of Arabidopsis thaliana
